# Reactable CLI — plan of record

**Status:** v0.1 shipped — agent CLI + deck script DSL + HyperFrames bridge.

Home: [[index]]. Agent skill: `skill/SKILL.md`.

## Why a CLI (not MCP)

Agents in Cursor / Claude Code already run shell commands. A flat **`reactable`
verb tree** plus a **project-local skill** gives:

- deterministic file edits (`deck.work`, `edit.json`, HF HTML)
- JSON stdout (`--json`) for machine reads
- no extra server beyond the existing nexus sidecar

MCP can be added later as a thin wrapper over the same verbs.

## Architecture

```
Agent (Cursor / Claude Code)
    │  reactable decks|takes|stage|serve|plan …
    ▼
cli/bin/reactable.ts  ──writes──► decks/*/deck.work  (slide do / script do)
    │                              takes/*
    │  POST /reactable/stage  (open native preview)
    │  curl /reactable/deck
    ▼
nexus (:4020)  present/api.work
    │  /reactable/deck  /reactable/exec  /reactable/stage  /reactable/labs/*
    ▼
present/index.work  ──►  StageWindow WKWebView  ──►  Aperture stage.mov
         ▲                      │
         └──── same URL ────────┘   preview = record
```

**Stage rule:** preview and capture share one WKWebView. Agents use
`reactable stage open --deck <slug>` — never `open` a browser URL for decks.

Weave reference: [[skill/references/stage-pipeline]].

## Deck DSL

Native `.work` blocks — `slide do`, `script do`, `preload do`, `client :unit`.
See [[skill/references/deck-dsl]].

- `deck.open` — stage boot
- `record.start` — Swift fires before capture
- `slide.enter` / `slide.leave` — navigation hooks
- `at` — delayed execution (seconds)

Dev servers: `detach: true` + `cwd` under deck folder.

## Post lanes

| Lane | Tool | When |
|------|------|------|
| Fast | `composite.py` / `takes render` | PIP, zoom, captions, aspects |
| Rich | `takes hf init` + HyperFrames | agent-authored motion/overlays |

